```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Set size for better visibility
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))

# Scatter plot of cells showing their spatial distribution, colored by their `subclass`
sns.scatterplot(
    data=df,
    x='x',
    y='y',
    hue='subclass',
    palette='hsv',
    s=10,
    alpha=0.6
)
plt.title('Spatial Distribution of Cell Subclasses')
plt.xlabel('X Coordinate')
plt.ylabel('Y Coordinate')
plt.legend(title='Subclass', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Heatmap of cell spatial density using a 2D histogram
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 10))

# Use hexbin for a better heatmap visualization
plt.hexbin(df['x'], df['y'], gridsize=100, cmap='Blues', mincnt=1)
plt.title('Density Heatmap of Cells')
plt.xlabel('X Coordinate')
plt.ylabel('Y Coordinate')
plt.colorbar(label='Cell Density')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
```
